            "content": "# Factory platform overview\n\nFactory is an AI-powered software engineering platform built around **Droid**, an autonomous coding agent that runs in the terminal, desktop, and browser. Engineers interact with Droid to write code, debug issues, run tests, and manage development workflows. The platform handles authentication, billing, LLM orchestration, and integrations with tools like GitHub, Linear, and Slack.\n\n## What this repo contains\n\nThis is the Factory monorepo (`factory-mono`), a TypeScript codebase using npm workspaces and Turborepo. It contains everything needed to run the platform:\n\n- **CLI and daemon** (`apps/cli`) -- the Droid terminal interface and background process, built with Bun and Ink (React for the terminal)\n- **Web app** (`apps/web`) -- the browser-based Droid chat interface, built with Vite and React\n- **Desktop app** (`apps/desktop`) -- an Electron wrapper around the web app with native system integration\n- **Backend API** (`apps/backend`) -- a Next.js API server handling auth, sessions, billing, LLM proxying, and integrations\n- **Signal and Relay** (`apps/signal`, `apps/relay`) -- real-time WebSocket infrastructure for session communication\n- **Shared packages** -- core UI components (`@factory/core-ui`), shared frontend code (`@factory/frontend`), AI agent logic (`@factory/droid-core`), types and protocol schemas (`@factory/common`), and more\n- **Infrastructure** (`infra/`) -- OpenTofu (Terraform) configurations for AWS deployment\n\n## Who uses what\n\n| Audience | Primary touchpoint |\n|---|---|\n| Engineers using Factory | `droid` CLI, desktop app, or web app |\n| Platform engineers | Backend API, infrastructure, shared packages |\n| Frontend engineers | Web/desktop apps, `@factory/frontend`, `@factory/core-ui` |\n| CLI/agent engineers | `apps/cli`, `@factory/droid-core`, `@factory/common` protocol |\n\n## Quick links\n\n- [Architecture](./architecture.md) -- system components and how they connect\n- [Getting started](./getting-started.md) -- setup, build, and run instructions\n- [Glossary](./glossary.md) -- project-specific terms\n- [How to contribute](../how-to-contribute/index.md) -- PR process, coding conventions\n- [Apps](../apps/index.md) -- all deployable applications\n- [Packages](../packages/index.md) -- shared libraries\n- [Features](../features/index.md) -- cross-cutting capabilities\n",
