            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory follows a client-daemon-cloud architecture. The CLI, desktop app, and web app all communicate with a local daemon process, which manages sessions and proxies requests to the backend API.\n\n## System diagram\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph Clients\n        CLI[Droid CLI]\n        Desktop[Desktop App]\n        WebApp[Web App]\n    end\n\n    subgraph Local\n        Daemon[Daemon Process]\n    end\n\n    subgraph Cloud\n        Backend[Backend API<br/>Next.js]\n        Signal[Signal Server]\n        Relay[Relay Server]\n        E2B[E2B Sandboxes]\n        LLMProviders[LLM Providers<br/>Anthropic/OpenAI/Google]\n    end\n\n    subgraph Data\n        Firestore[(Firestore)]\n        S3[(AWS S3)]\n    end\n\n    CLI -->|stdin/stdout JSON-RPC| Daemon\n    Desktop -->|spawns & manages| Daemon\n    WebApp -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| Daemon\n\n    Daemon -->|HTTPS| Backend\n    Daemon -->|WebSocket| Signal\n    Daemon -->|WebSocket| Relay\n\n    Backend -->|API calls| LLMProviders\n    Backend -->|read/write| Firestore\n    Backend -->|file storage| S3\n    Backend -->|sandbox mgmt| E2B\n\n    Signal -->|real-time events| WebApp\n    Relay -->|session relay| Daemon\n```\n\n## Communication protocol\n\nThe platform uses JSON-RPC as its communication protocol across all layers:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI as CLI (Ink TUI)\n    participant Daemon as Daemon\n    participant Backend as Backend API\n\n    User->>CLI: Types message\n    CLI->>Daemon: JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\n    Daemon->>Backend: HTTPS API calls\n    Backend->>Backend: LLM proxy + tool orchestration\n    Backend-->>Daemon: Streaming response\n    Daemon-->>CLI: JSON-RPC notifications\n    CLI-->>User: Renders TUI output\n```\n\nProtocol schemas live in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` (CLI-side) and `packages/common/src/daemon/` (daemon-side). The shared envelope types are in `packages/common/src/shared/schemas.ts`. Protocol version tracking is enforced by CI via `apps/scripts/src/protocol-manifest/`.\n\n## Layer breakdown\n\n| Layer | Location | Runtime | Role |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| CLI | `apps/cli` | Bun | TUI interface, agent loop, tool execution |\n| Daemon | `packages/daemon-core`, `apps/cli/src/commands/daemon.ts` | Bun | Background process, session management, relay connection |\n| Web app | `apps/web` | Vite/React | Browser-based chat interface |\n| Desktop | `apps/desktop` | Electron | Native wrapper, daemon lifecycle management |\n| Backend | `apps/backend` | Next.js (Node) | REST API, LLM proxy, auth, billing, integrations |\n| Signal | `apps/signal` | Bun | WebSocket server for real-time frontend events |\n| Relay | `apps/relay` | Bun | WebSocket relay between daemon instances |\n\n## Data stores\n\n- **Firestore** -- primary database for users, organizations, sessions, and configuration. Models defined in `packages/models/src/`\n- **AWS S3** -- file storage for bug reports, session artifacts, and binary releases\n- **Redis** (via relay) -- ephemeral session state and pub/sub for real-time messaging\n\n## External services\n\n| Service | Purpose | Integration point |\n|---|---|---|\n| WorkOS | Authentication (AuthKit) | `apps/backend/src/services/workos/` |\n| Orb | Usage-based billing | `apps/backend/src/services/orb/` |\n| Statsig | Feature flags | `packages/common/src/feature-flags/` |\n| Sentry | Error tracking | `packages/logging/`, `apps/cli/src/sentry.config.ts` |\n| E2B | Cloud sandboxes | `apps/backend/src/services/e2b/` |\n| GitHub/Linear/Slack | Integrations | `apps/backend/src/services/integrations/` |\n| Anthropic/OpenAI/Google | LLM providers | `packages/droid-core/src/llms/` |\n\n## Package dependency graph\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    CLI[apps/cli] --> DroidCore[droid-core]\n    CLI --> Common[common]\n    CLI --> DaemonCore[daemon-core]\n    CLI --> Logging[logging]\n\n    WebApp[apps/web] --> Frontend[frontend]\n    WebApp --> CoreUI[core-ui]\n    WebApp --> Common\n\n    Desktop[apps/desktop] --> Frontend\n    Desktop --> CoreUI\n\n    Frontend --> CoreUI\n    Frontend --> Common\n    Frontend --> ComponentLib[component-library]\n\n    Backend[apps/backend] --> Common\n    Backend --> Models[models]\n    Backend --> Services[services]\n    Backend --> Logging\n\n    DroidCore --> Common\n    DaemonCore --> Common\n    DaemonCore --> Logging\n\n    ComponentLib --> CoreUI\n    ComponentLib --> Common\n```\n\nKey architectural constraint: `@factory/core-ui` is the mandatory design system. All UI code must use its primitives (`Box`, `Button`, `Input`, etc.) rather than raw HTML elements.\n",
