            "content": "# Getting started\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js 18.x** (see `.nvmrc`)\n- **npm 11.x** (bundled with the monorepo's `packageManager` field)\n- **Bun** (required for CLI and daemon development)\n- **Git 2.39+**\n\n## Initial setup\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\nThe `postinstall` hook runs `turbo run setup`, which builds all packages and prepares the workspace.\n\n## Common commands\n\n| Command | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `npm run dev:web` | Starts backend, web, storybook, admin, and daemon |\n| `npm run dev:desktop` | Same as above plus the Electron desktop app |\n| `npm run build` | Builds all packages |\n| `npm run test` | Runs all tests (uses ~9 GB RAM; prefer filtering) |\n| `npm run typecheck` | TypeScript type checking |\n| `npm run fix` | Lint + auto-format (preferred over `npm run lint`) |\n| `npm run knip` | Detect unused exports |\n| `npm run clean` | Clear all caches |\n\nDo **not** run `npm run dev` at the root. It is intentionally disabled.\n\n## Filtering to specific packages\n\nTurborepo powers all build/test/lint scripts. You must use `--` before `--filter` or npm swallows the flag:\n\n```bash\n# Correct\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Wrong (runs ALL packages)\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common\n```\n\n## Running a single test file\n\n```bash\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## CLI development\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n```\n\nThis creates `droid-dev` (runs against hosted dev API) and `droid-localhost` (runs against local API). Changes to CLI source are immediately available via `droid-dev` without rebuilding.\n\nAfter modifying CLI or daemon code:\n1. Rebuild: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Restart the daemon process\n3. Start a new session (old sessions won't pick up changes)\n\n## Dev server logs\n\nEach app streams output to both console and a log file:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| Backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| Admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| Desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| Daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\nRuntime logs go to `~/.factory-dev/logs/` (dev) or `~/.factory/logs/` (prod).\n\n## Storybook\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n```\n\nUseful for previewing `@factory/core-ui` components and the component library.\n",
