            "content": "# Glossary\n\n| Term | Definition |\n|---|---|\n| **Droid** | The AI coding agent product. Refers to both the CLI tool (`droid` command) and the agent system as a whole. |\n| **Session** | A single conversation between a user and Droid. Sessions track message history, tool calls, and context. Stored in Firestore. |\n| **Daemon** | A background process (`droid daemon`) that manages sessions, connects to the relay, and bridges the CLI to the backend. |\n| **Mission** | A multi-step autonomous task where Droid decomposes a large goal into sub-tasks and executes them, potentially spawning sub-agents. |\n| **Skill** | A reusable prompt template that gives Droid specialized knowledge for a domain (e.g., \"wiki generation\", \"CLI testing\"). Stored as markdown files in `.factory/skills/`. |\n| **Custom droid** | A user-defined agent configuration specifying model, tools, and behavior. Stored in `.factory/droids/`. |\n| **MCP** | Model Context Protocol. An open standard for connecting AI agents to external tools and data sources. Factory supports MCP servers as tool providers. |\n| **Exec mode** | Non-interactive CLI mode where Droid runs a task to completion without user input (`droid exec`). |\n| **BYOK** | Bring Your Own Key. Users can provide their own LLM API keys instead of using Factory's. |\n| **Relay** | A WebSocket server that connects daemon instances to enable features like session sharing and remote access. |\n| **Signal** | A WebSocket server that pushes real-time events to the web frontend. |\n| **E2B** | A cloud sandbox provider. Factory uses E2B to run Droid sessions in isolated environments. |\n| **WorkOS** | The authentication provider. Factory uses WorkOS AuthKit for user login and organization management. |\n| **Orb** | The usage-based billing provider. Tracks token consumption and subscription tiers. |\n| **Statsig** | Feature flag service. Flags are defined in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. |\n| **Core UI** | The `@factory/core-ui` package. The mandatory design system with primitives like `Box`, `Button`, `Input`. All UI must use these instead of raw HTML. |\n| **MetaError** | The standard error class for internal errors. Carries structured metadata for Sentry reporting. Never throw vanilla `Error`. |\n| **Readiness** | A system that analyzes a repository's configuration to determine how well it's set up for Droid to work with. |\n| **Agent loop** | The core cycle in the CLI where Droid receives a user message, sends it to an LLM, processes tool calls, and renders output. Implemented in `useAgent.ts`. |\n| **JSON-RPC** | The wire protocol used between CLI, daemon, and frontend. Messages follow the JSON-RPC 2.0 spec. |\n| **Protocol manifest** | A CI-enforced checksum of the daemon/CLI protocol schemas, ensuring backward compatibility. |\n| **Turborepo** | The build orchestrator that manages task dependencies across the monorepo's npm workspaces. |\n",
