            "content": "# CLI\n\nActive contributors: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, shashank-factory, theo, Leo Tchourakov\n\nThe Droid CLI is the primary interface for Factory. It runs as a terminal application built with Bun and Ink (React for the terminal), providing a TUI where engineers interact with an AI coding agent. The CLI also includes a daemon mode for background session management and an exec mode for non-interactive task execution.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/src/\n  index.ts              # CLI entry point, Commander.js program setup\n  main.tsx              # TUI application bootstrap\n  app.tsx               # Root React component (4710 lines)\n  commands/             # 50+ slash commands\n  components/           # Ink React components for TUI rendering\n  hooks/                # React hooks (agent loop, LLM streaming, tools)\n  services/             # Session, settings, MCP, mission services\n  tools/                # Tool executors (file, shell, git, browser)\n  exec/                 # Exec mode (non-interactive) runner\n  mcp/                  # MCP server management\n  agent/                # Agent configuration and adapters\n  llm-proxy/            # Local LLM proxy layer\n  models/               # Data model converters\n  prompt-tuning/        # Prompt optimization system\n  skills/               # Built-in skill definitions\n  i18n/                 # Internationalization\n  utils/                # 200+ utility modules\n```\n\n## Entry points\n\nThe CLI has two main entry points:\n\n1. **`src/index.ts`** -- Commander.js program that parses CLI arguments. Handles top-level commands like `droid exec`, `droid daemon`, `droid login`, etc. For interactive sessions, it calls `main()`.\n2. **`src/main.tsx`** -- bootstraps the Ink TUI application. Initializes i18n, feature flags, telemetry, MCP services, and renders the root `<App>` component.\n\n## Agent loop\n\nThe core interaction cycle lives in React hooks:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    UserInput[User types message] --> useAgent[useAgent hook]\n    useAgent --> useLLM[useLLMStreaming]\n    useLLM --> Provider[LLM Provider API]\n    Provider --> StreamResponse[Streaming response]\n    StreamResponse --> ToolCheck{Tool calls?}\n    ToolCheck -->|Yes| useToolExec[useToolExecution]\n    useToolExec --> ToolResult[Execute tool]\n    ToolResult --> useLLM\n    ToolCheck -->|No| Render[Render to TUI]\n    Render --> UserInput\n```\n\n- **`useAgent.ts`** -- orchestrates the conversation loop. Sends messages, processes responses, manages context.\n- **`useLLMStreaming.ts`** -- handles streaming LLM responses from multiple providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google).\n- **`useToolExecution.ts`** -- executes tool calls requested by the LLM (file edits, shell commands, web search, etc.).\n- **`ConversationStateManager.ts`** -- tracks conversation history, manages context windows, handles message compaction.\n\nSee [Agent loop](./agent-loop.md) for details. See [Commands](./commands.md) for the full command reference.\n\n## Modes of operation\n\n| Mode | Entry | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| Interactive TUI | `droid` | Full terminal UI with chat, tool rendering, keyboard shortcuts |\n| Exec mode | `droid exec \"task\"` | Non-interactive: runs a task to completion and exits |\n| Daemon | `droid daemon` | Background process managing sessions and relay connections |\n| SSH | `droid ssh` | Remote session via SSH tunnel |\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Commander.js program, CLI argument parsing |\n| `src/main.tsx` | TUI bootstrap, feature flags, telemetry init |\n| `src/app.tsx` | Root Ink component, main application state |\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | Agent conversation loop |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | LLM streaming integration |\n| `src/hooks/useToolExecution.ts` | Tool call execution |\n| `src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Conversation history and context |\n| `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle management |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx` | Exec mode runner |\n| `src/commands/daemon.ts` | Daemon mode implementation |\n",
