            "content": "# Agent loop\n\nActive contributors: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, shashank-factory\n\nThe agent loop is the core cycle that powers Droid conversations. When a user sends a message, the loop sends it to an LLM, processes any tool calls in the response, feeds results back to the LLM, and repeats until the LLM produces a final text response.\n\n## Flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant App as App Component\n    participant Agent as useAgent\n    participant LLM as useLLMStreaming\n    participant Tools as useToolExecution\n    participant State as ConversationStateManager\n\n    User->>App: Types message\n    App->>Agent: Submit message\n    Agent->>State: Add user message to history\n    Agent->>LLM: Stream completion request\n    LLM-->>Agent: Streaming tokens + tool calls\n    \n    alt Has tool calls\n        Agent->>Tools: Execute tool calls\n        Tools-->>Agent: Tool results\n        Agent->>State: Add tool results\n        Agent->>LLM: Continue with tool results\n    else Text response only\n        Agent->>State: Add assistant message\n        Agent-->>App: Render response\n    end\n```\n\n## Key hooks\n\n### useAgent\n\nDefined in `src/hooks/useAgent.ts`. Orchestrates the full conversation loop:\n- Accepts user messages and submits them to the LLM\n- Manages the request-response cycle including multi-turn tool use\n- Handles streaming state (loading, error, cancellation)\n- Coordinates with the conversation state manager for context window management\n\n### useLLMStreaming\n\nDefined in `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` with core logic in `src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts`. Handles:\n- Multi-provider streaming (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google) through a unified interface\n- Token-by-token response processing\n- Tool call extraction from streaming responses\n- Error handling and retry logic\n- BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) support\n\n### useToolExecution\n\nDefined in `src/hooks/useToolExecution.ts`. Manages:\n- Tool call dispatch to the appropriate executor\n- Permission checks before execution\n- Parallel and sequential tool execution\n- Result formatting for LLM consumption\n- Tool cancellation and timeout handling\n\n## Conversation state\n\n`ConversationStateManager` in `src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` tracks:\n- Full message history (user, assistant, tool messages)\n- Context window size management (compaction when history grows too large)\n- System prompt assembly (base prompt + skills + project context)\n- Message branching (rewind/fork support)\n\n## Tool system\n\nTools are registered through `src/tools/`. Each tool has:\n- A description (shown to the LLM so it knows when to use it)\n- An executor function that performs the action\n- A TUI component for rendering tool execution in the terminal\n\nThe tool registry in `src/tools/tui.ts` manages available tools. Tools can be dynamically registered via MCP servers or skill configurations.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | Main agent loop orchestration |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | LLM streaming interface |\n| `src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` | Core streaming logic |\n| `src/hooks/useToolExecution.ts` | Tool call execution |\n| `src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Conversation history management |\n| `src/tools/tui.ts` | Tool registry for TUI mode |\n| `src/tools/client.ts` | Tool client abstraction |\n",
