            "content": "# Backend\n\nActive contributors: Alvin Sng, factory-octavian, Nikita Lilichenko, factory-sherry, Leo Tchourakov\n\nThe backend is a Next.js 15 application that serves as the REST API for the Factory platform. It handles authentication, session storage, LLM proxying, billing, and third-party integrations. The web UI in this app is deprecated -- `apps/web` is the current frontend.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/src/\n  api/                  # Next.js API route handlers\n  app/                  # Next.js App Router pages and layouts\n  middleware.ts         # Request middleware (auth, rate limiting, CORS)\n  routes.ts             # Frontend route definitions\n  constants.ts          # Application constants\n  instrumentation.ts    # Sentry instrumentation\n  features/             # Backend feature modules\n    droids/             # Droid configuration management\n    feature-flags/      # Server-side feature flag evaluation\n    integrations/       # Integration configuration\n    llm/                # LLM proxy and model management\n    prompts/            # Prompt templates\n    workspace/          # Workspace management\n  services/             # External service integrations\n  utils/                # Helper utilities\n  env/                  # Environment configuration\n```\n\n## Middleware\n\n`src/middleware.ts` handles request processing before routes:\n- Authentication via WorkOS session tokens\n- Rate limiting\n- CORS configuration\n- Request logging\n\n## API structure\n\nAPI routes live under `src/api/` and `src/app/api/` following Next.js conventions. Key endpoint groups include:\n- Session CRUD and message history\n- LLM proxy endpoints for streaming completions\n- Authentication (login, logout, token refresh)\n- Billing and subscription management\n- Integration configuration (GitHub, Linear, Slack)\n- Webhook receivers\n- File upload and download\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Auth, rate limiting, CORS middleware |\n| `src/routes.ts` | Frontend route definitions |\n| `src/instrumentation.ts` | Sentry error tracking setup |\n| `src/features/llm/` | LLM proxy and model routing |\n| `src/features/droids/` | Droid configuration API |\n| `src/features/feature-flags/` | Statsig feature flag evaluation |\n\nSee [Backend services](./services.md) for the service layer.\n",
