            "content": "# Web app\n\nActive contributors: Alvin Sng, Nikita Lilichenko, Andrei Savin, Ricky S, factory-sherry\n\nThe web app is the browser-based interface for Droid, built with Vite and React 19. It provides a chat interface where users can interact with Droid sessions, manage settings, and view session history.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe app is thin -- most UI logic lives in `@factory/frontend` and `@factory/component-library`. The web app handles routing, authentication, and configuration.\n\n```\napps/web/src/\n  main.tsx              # Vite entry point\n  auth/                 # WorkOS AuthKit integration\n  config/               # App configuration\n  types/                # TypeScript type definitions\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nAuthentication uses WorkOS AuthKit via `@workos-inc/authkit-react`. The auth flow:\n1. User navigates to the app\n2. AuthKit checks for an existing session\n3. If unauthenticated, redirects to WorkOS-hosted login\n4. On return, the app receives a session token\n5. The token is used for all backend API calls\n\n## Daemon connection\n\nThe web app connects to the local daemon via WebSocket using `DaemonSessionController` from `@factory/frontend`. This controller:\n- Establishes a JSON-RPC connection over WebSocket\n- Creates and manages sessions\n- Sends user messages and receives streaming responses\n- Handles reconnection and error recovery\n\n## Testing\n\nE2E tests use Playwright. Configuration is in `packages/frontend/` since tests cover shared frontend behavior:\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n```\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main.tsx` | Vite entry point, React root mount |\n| `src/auth/` | WorkOS AuthKit provider setup |\n| `src/config/` | Environment-specific configuration |\n",
