            "content": "# Common\n\nActive contributors: factory-sherry, factory-octavian, Luke Alvoeiro, l30t, Abhay Singhal\n\n`@factory/common` is the shared type contract layer for the entire platform. It defines API types, protocol schemas, enums, feature flags, and domain types that are imported by nearly every other package and app.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n  agent/                # Agent-related types\n  agentReadiness/       # Repository readiness types\n  api/                  # API type definitions by service\n  automations/          # Automation workflow types\n  billing/              # Billing and subscription types\n  cli/                  # CLI-specific types\n  daemon/               # Daemon protocol schemas\n  desktop/              # Desktop app types\n  documents/            # Document types\n  droid/                # Droid/CLI protocol schemas\n  events/               # Event type definitions\n  feature-flags/        # Feature flag constants and types\n  images/               # Image-related types\n  integrations/         # Integration types (GitHub, Linear, Slack, etc.)\n  llm/                  # LLM model and provider types\n  memory/               # Memory/context types\n  node/                 # Node-specific types\n  organization/         # Organization and user types\n  policy/               # Policy and permissions types\n  relay/                # Relay protocol types\n  repositories/         # Repository types\n  security/             # Security-related types\n  session/              # Session types and schemas\n  sessionV2/            # Next-gen session types\n  settings/             # Settings types\n  shared/               # Shared schemas (JSON-RPC envelope)\n  tags/                 # Tagging types\n  terminal/             # Terminal types\n  timeline/             # Timeline types\n  tools/                # Tool definition types\n  ui/                   # UI-related types\n  updater/              # Update types\n  usage/                # Usage tracking types\n  wiki/                 # Wiki types\n  workspaces/           # Workspace types\n```\n\n## API type conventions\n\nAPI types are organized by service under `src/api/`. Each service directory contains a `types.ts` file with request/response types. This pattern is enforced by ESLint and documented in `docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md`.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flag constants live in `src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. Each flag has a `displayName`, `statsigName` (matching the Statsig console), and `defaultValue`. Flags are consumed by both frontend (`useFeatureFlagValue`) and backend (`getFeatureFlagInstance`).\n\n## Protocol schemas\n\nSee [Protocol](./protocol.md) for the JSON-RPC communication protocol between CLI, daemon, and frontend.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | Feature flag definitions |\n| `src/shared/schemas.ts` | JSON-RPC envelope types |\n| `src/droid/schemas/` | CLI-side protocol schemas |\n| `src/daemon/` | Daemon-side protocol schemas |\n| `src/api/` | API type contracts by service |\n| `src/integrations/` | Integration type definitions |\n| `src/session/` | Session types and enums |\n",
