            "content": "# Protocol\n\nActive contributors: factory-sherry, factory-octavian, Luke Alvoeiro, l30t\n\nThe Factory platform uses JSON-RPC 2.0 as its wire protocol for communication between the CLI, daemon, and frontend. Protocol schemas are defined in `@factory/common` and enforced by CI.\n\n## Protocol layers\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    CLI -->|stdin/stdout JSON-RPC| Daemon\n    WebApp -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| Daemon\n    Desktop -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| Daemon\n```\n\nEach layer has its own schema directory:\n\n| Layer | Schema location | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| Shared | `src/shared/schemas.ts` | JSON-RPC envelope types used by all layers |\n| CLI/Droid | `src/droid/schemas/` | Schemas for CLI-to-daemon communication |\n| Daemon | `src/daemon/` | Schemas for daemon-side protocol handling |\n\n## Envelope types\n\nThe shared envelope in `src/shared/schemas.ts` defines the base JSON-RPC message structure:\n- Request messages with method name and params\n- Response messages with result or error\n- Notification messages (one-way, no response expected)\n\n## Session notifications\n\n`SessionNotificationType` enum in `src/droid/enums.ts` lists all notification types the CLI can send to the daemon/frontend:\n- Message events (new message, message update, streaming tokens)\n- Tool execution events (tool start, progress, completion)\n- Session lifecycle events (session created, resumed, ended)\n- Status updates (connection state, model changes)\n\n## Protocol versioning\n\n`FACTORY_PROTOCOL_VERSION` in `src/droid/schemas/constants.ts` tracks the current protocol version. When protocol schemas change, this version must be bumped.\n\nThe **protocol manifest** system in `apps/scripts/src/protocol-manifest/` generates a checksum of all protocol schemas. CI runs this check on every PR to detect breaking protocol changes. If a schema changes without a corresponding version bump, the CI check fails.\n\nThis prevents accidentally shipping a CLI that can't communicate with the daemon, or vice versa.\n\n## Adding a new notification type\n\n1. Add the type to `SessionNotificationType` in `src/droid/enums.ts`\n2. Define the schema in `src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. Add a handler in the frontend's `DaemonSessionController.ts`\n4. Bump `FACTORY_PROTOCOL_VERSION` if it's a breaking change\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/shared/schemas.ts` | JSON-RPC envelope definitions |\n| `src/droid/enums.ts` | Session notification type enum |\n| `src/droid/schemas/cli.ts` | CLI-side notification schemas |\n| `src/droid/schemas/constants.ts` | Protocol version constant |\n| `src/daemon/` | Daemon-side protocol schemas |\n",
