            "content": "# Droid core\n\nActive contributors: Luke Alvoeiro, l30t, Alvin Sng, factory-sherry, Varin Nair\n\n`@factory/droid-core` is the AI agent core library. It handles LLM provider integrations, tool definitions, prompt management, message processing, and streaming. This package is consumed primarily by `apps/cli` but is designed to be reusable for any Droid-powered application.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n  api/                  # API client for Factory backend\n  automations/          # Automated workflow definitions\n  core/                 # Core abstractions and base classes\n  droids/               # Droid configuration loading and management\n  feature-flags/        # Feature flag integration\n  llms/                 # LLM provider implementations\n  machine-connection/   # Machine connection management\n  messages/             # Message handling and formatting\n  prompts/              # System prompt assembly\n  streaming/            # Streaming response processing\n  test-utils/           # Test helpers\n  tools/                # Tool interface definitions\n```\n\n## LLM integration\n\nThe `llms/` directory contains the multi-provider abstraction layer. It supports:\n- **Anthropic** (Claude models)\n- **OpenAI** (GPT models)\n- **Google** (Gemini models)\n\nEach provider implements a common interface for sending messages and processing streaming responses. The streaming layer in `streaming/` handles token-by-token processing, tool call extraction, and error recovery.\n\nSee [LLM integration](./llm-integration.md) for details.\n\n## Tool system\n\n`tools/` defines the tool interface that Droid uses to interact with the development environment. Tools include file operations, shell commands, web search, browser automation, and more. The tool definitions here are consumed by the CLI, which provides the actual executors.\n\n## Prompt management\n\n`prompts/` handles system prompt assembly. The system prompt includes:\n- Base instructions for the AI agent\n- Project context (repository structure, conventions)\n- Active skill instructions\n- Tool descriptions\n- Custom droid configuration\n\n## Message handling\n\n`messages/` processes conversation messages between the user, assistant, and tools. It handles format conversion between the internal message format and provider-specific formats.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/llms/` | Multi-provider LLM abstraction |\n| `src/streaming/` | Streaming response processing |\n| `src/tools/` | Tool interface definitions |\n| `src/prompts/` | System prompt assembly |\n| `src/messages/` | Message format handling |\n| `src/droids/` | Droid configuration management |\n| `src/api/` | Factory API client |\n",
