            "content": "# Frontend\n\nActive contributors: Andrei Savin, factory-sherry, Alvin Sng, factory-octavian, Nikita Lilichenko\n\n`@factory/frontend` is the shared React feature layer consumed by both the web and desktop apps. It contains feature modules, hooks, services, routing, and layouts that power the Factory UI.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n  api/                  # API client utilities\n  app/                  # App-level configuration\n  auth/                 # Authentication hooks and providers\n  errors/               # Error handling components\n  features/             # Feature modules (see below)\n  hooks/                # Shared React hooks\n  index.ts              # Package exports\n  layouts/              # Page layout components\n  router/               # Route definitions and guards\n  services/             # Service layer (session controller)\n  types/                # Shared type definitions\n  utils/                # Utility functions\n  views/                # View components\n```\n\n## Features\n\nThe `features/` directory contains the main UI feature modules. See [Features](./features.md) for details.\n\n## Session controller\n\nThe most important service is `DaemonSessionController` in `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`. It manages the WebSocket JSON-RPC connection to the daemon, handling:\n- Session creation and resumption\n- Message sending and streaming response reception\n- Notification handling (tool execution, status updates)\n- Reconnection logic\n\n## Routing\n\n`src/router/` defines the application routes and navigation guards. Routes map to views for sessions, settings, onboarding, and other pages.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Daemon WebSocket connection |\n| `src/features/` | Feature modules |\n| `src/auth/` | Authentication hooks |\n| `src/router/` | Route definitions |\n| `src/layouts/` | Page layout components |\n| `src/hooks/` | Shared React hooks |\n",
