            "content": "# Frontend features\n\nActive contributors: Andrei Savin, factory-sherry, Alvin Sng, factory-octavian, Nikita Lilichenko\n\nEach directory under `packages/frontend/src/features/` is a self-contained feature module with its own components, hooks, and state management.\n\n## Feature catalog\n\n| Feature | Directory | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| Sessions | `sessions/` | Core session UI: chat interface, message rendering, session list, session sidebar. The largest feature module with hooks and sub-modules for message handling. |\n| Settings | `settings/` | User and organization settings: general, integrations, billing, API keys, security, agent readiness, cloud templates. |\n| Analytics | `analytics/` | Usage analytics dashboards and charts. |\n| Auth | `auth/` | Authentication state management and login/logout flows. |\n| Automations | `automations/` | Automated workflow configuration and monitoring. |\n| Feature flags | `feature-flags/` | Client-side feature flag evaluation with Statsig. |\n| Missions | `missions/` | Mission UI: task decomposition view, sub-agent progress tracking. |\n| Onboarding | `onboarding/` | New user onboarding flow. |\n| Terminal | `terminal/` | Terminal emulator component for session output. |\n| Wiki | `wiki/` | Wiki viewer for generated documentation. |\n| Banner | `banner/` | Notification banners (announcements, warnings). |\n| Attribution | `attribution/` | Content attribution tracking. |\n| Debug | `debug/` | Debug tools and panels. |\n| Error | `error/` | Error boundary and error display components. |\n| GA Analytics | `ga-analytics/` | Google Analytics integration. |\n| Health | `health/` | System health monitoring UI. |\n| Home | `home/` | Home/dashboard page. |\n| Referral | `referral/` | Referral program UI. |\n| Support | `support/` | Support and help components. |\n| Utility | `utility/` | Shared utility components. |\n\n## Sessions deep dive\n\nThe sessions feature is the largest and most complex. It lives in `features/sessions/` and includes:\n- **hooks/** -- React hooks for session state, message streaming, and UI interactions\n- **modules/** -- Sub-modules for different aspects of session management (message list, input, sidebar)\n- **components/** -- Session-specific React components\n\nThe session UI renders Droid conversations, handles user input, displays tool execution results, and manages session history navigation.\n\n## Settings deep dive\n\nThe settings feature in `features/settings/` covers multiple settings pages:\n- General settings (display, language, model preferences)\n- Integration management (connect/disconnect GitHub, Linear, Slack)\n- Billing (subscription tier, usage, payment methods)\n- API keys (BYOK configuration)\n- Security (access controls, audit logs)\n- Agent readiness (repository configuration analysis)\n",
