            "content": "# Core UI\n\nActive contributors: Andrei Savin, factory-sherry, Alvin Sng, Nikita Lilichenko\n\n`@factory/core-ui` is the mandatory design system for all Factory UI development. Every frontend component must use its primitives instead of raw HTML elements.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/core-ui/src/\n  primitives/           # Layout and form primitives (30+ components)\n  colors/               # Semantic color system (light/dark modes)\n  typography/           # Font system and text components\n  tokens/               # Design tokens (spacing, borders, shadows)\n  icons/                # Icon components\n  fonts/                # Font files and loading\n  form/                 # Form-specific components\n  hooks/                # UI hooks\n  styles/               # Global styles and CSS utilities\n  utils/                # UI utility functions\n  index.ts              # Package exports\n```\n\n## Primitives\n\nThe `primitives/` directory contains 30+ components:\n- **Layout**: `Box`, `Flex`, `Grid` -- foundational layout containers\n- **Forms**: `Button`, `Input`, `Dropdown`, `Checkbox`, `Switch`, `TextArea`\n- **Typography**: `Header`, `Text`, `Label`\n- **Interactive**: `Collapsible`, `Toast`, `Tooltip`, `Modal`, `Popover`\n- **Navigation**: `Tabs`, `Breadcrumb`\n- **Data**: `Table`, `Badge`, `Tag`\n\n## Color system\n\nThe color system in `colors/` uses semantic tokens that adapt to light and dark modes. Colors are referenced via `colors.semantics` -- never hardcode hex values. The system defines:\n- Surface colors (backgrounds, cards, overlays)\n- Text colors (primary, secondary, disabled)\n- Interactive colors (buttons, links, focus rings)\n- Status colors (success, warning, error, info)\n\n## Usage rules\n\n- Always import from `@factory/core-ui`, never use raw HTML elements\n- Use `Box` instead of `<div>`, `Button` instead of `<button>`, `Input` instead of `<input>`\n- Use `colors.semantics` for all color values\n- Preview components in Storybook (`npm run storybook`)\n",
