            "content": "# Other packages\n\n## Logging\n\n`@factory/logging` provides structured logging with automatic secret scrubbing and Sentry integration. Exports `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logException` functions and the `MetaError` / `ResponseErrorXXX` error classes. All error throwing must use these classes, never vanilla `Error`. Located in `packages/logging/`.\n\n## Models\n\n`@factory/models` defines Firestore data models in `packages/models/src/`. Contains model definitions for organizations, sessions, referrals, integrations, API keys, promotions, events, and workspaces. Each model directory has type definitions and optional converter utilities.\n\n## Services\n\n`@factory/services` in `packages/services/src/` provides a shared service layer for settings management (`SettingsManager`, `FactorySettingsFolder`), plugin management, session search, and feature flag evaluation. The settings system handles both global and project-level configuration.\n\n## ESLint config\n\n`@factory/eslint-config` in `packages/eslint-config/` contains 57 custom ESLint rules under `rules/` plus shared configurations (`base.js`, `frontend.js`, `backend.js`, `factory.js`). Custom rules enforce file organization (enums in `enums.ts`, types in `types.ts`), import restrictions, and Factory-specific conventions.\n\n## Updater\n\n`@factory/updater` in `packages/updater/` handles CLI and daemon auto-updates. Checks for new versions, downloads binaries, and manages the update installation process.\n\n## Utils\n\n`@factory/utils` in `packages/utils/` contains shared utility functions used across the monorepo.\n\n## Environment\n\n`@factory/environment` in `packages/environment/` provides typed access to environment variables. Replaces direct `process.env` access with a strongly-typed system. ESLint rule `no-direct-process-env` enforces migration to this package.\n\n## Runtime\n\n`@factory/runtime` in `packages/runtime/` provides runtime utilities including authentication helpers (`getAuthedUser`).\n\n## Daemon client\n\n`@factory/daemon-client` in `packages/daemon-client/` is the client library for communicating with the daemon process from web/desktop apps.\n\n## Droid SDK\n\n`@factory/droid-sdk` in `packages/droid-sdk/` is the SDK for building integrations with the Droid agent. Contains a client (`client.ts`, 3723 lines of tests) for programmatic Droid interaction.\n\n## MCP\n\n`@factory/mcp` in `packages/mcp/` provides Model Context Protocol integration for connecting external tool servers to Droid.\n\n## Signal core\n\n`@factory/signal-core` in `packages/signal-core/` contains the core library for the Signal WebSocket server.\n\n## Test utils\n\n`@factory/test-utils` in `packages/test-utils/` provides shared test utilities and helpers for the monorepo's test suites.\n",
