            "content": "# Sessions\n\nA session is the core workflow unit in Factory -- a single conversation between a user and Droid. Sessions track message history, tool calls, context, and metadata. They persist across CLI restarts and can be accessed from the web and desktop apps.\n\n## Session lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Created: User starts droid or /new\n    Created --> Active: First message sent\n    Active --> Active: Messages exchanged\n    Active --> Compacted: /compact or auto-compact\n    Compacted --> Active: Continue conversation\n    Active --> Forked: /fork\n    Active --> Ended: User quits or session expires\n    Ended --> Resumed: User resumes from history\n    Resumed --> Active\n```\n\n## Where sessions live\n\n| Layer | Location | Responsibility |\n|---|---|---|\n| CLI | `src/services/SessionService.ts`, `src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Local session state, conversation history |\n| Frontend | `src/features/sessions/`, `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Session UI, daemon communication |\n| Backend | Session API routes | Session persistence, metadata storage |\n| Common | `src/session/`, `src/sessionV2/` | Session type definitions |\n| Models | `src/session/` | Firestore session model |\n\n## Data flow\n\n1. User types a message in the CLI or web app\n2. The client sends a JSON-RPC request to the daemon\n3. The daemon routes it to the CLI process handling that session\n4. The CLI adds the message to `ConversationStateManager`, sends it to the LLM\n5. The LLM response (with possible tool calls) is processed\n6. Session state is persisted to Firestore via the backend API\n\n## Session storage\n\nSessions are stored in Firestore with:\n- Session ID, creation timestamp, last activity\n- Organization and user references\n- Message history (or a reference to compacted history)\n- Model configuration used\n- Tags and favorites\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` | CLI-side session lifecycle |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Conversation history |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Web/desktop session controller |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/` | Session UI components |\n| `packages/common/src/session/` | Session type definitions |\n",
