            "content": "# MCP integration\n\nModel Context Protocol (MCP) allows Droid to connect to external tool servers, expanding its capabilities beyond built-in tools. Users can add MCP servers that provide access to databases, APIs, design tools, and other systems.\n\n## How it works\n\n1. User adds an MCP server: `droid mcp add <name> <url> --type http`\n2. The CLI connects to the MCP server and discovers available tools\n3. Discovered tools are registered in the tool system alongside built-in tools\n4. The LLM can invoke MCP tools just like built-in tools\n5. Tool calls are routed to the MCP server, and results are returned to the LLM\n\n## Configuration\n\nMCP server configurations are stored in the user's settings. The `/mcp` command manages servers:\n- `/mcp add` -- add a new MCP server\n- `/mcp remove` -- remove a server\n- `/mcp list` -- list configured servers\n\nServer definitions can also be placed in `.factory/mcp.json` at the project level.\n\n## Implementation\n\n| Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/mcp/` | MCP service, server connection management |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/mcp/` | MCP slash commands |\n| `packages/mcp/` | MCP protocol client library |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/mcp/McpService.ts` | MCP service singleton |\n\nThe CLI uses `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` for the MCP protocol implementation.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/services/mcp/McpService.ts` | MCP service management |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/mcp/mcp.ts` | MCP command handler |\n| `packages/mcp/` | Protocol client library |\n",
