            "content": "# Missions\n\nMissions are multi-step autonomous tasks where Droid decomposes a large goal into sub-tasks and executes them. A mission can spawn sub-agents (worker droids) to handle individual tasks in parallel.\n\n## How missions work\n\n1. User describes a large task (e.g., \"refactor the auth system\")\n2. Droid creates a mission plan with discrete sub-tasks\n3. Each sub-task can be delegated to a worker sub-agent\n4. Sub-agents execute independently and report results\n5. The parent agent assembles results and continues\n\n## Commands\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/mission` | `commands/mission.ts` | Start a new mission |\n| `/missions` | `commands/missions.ts` | List active and past missions |\n| `/enter-mission` | `commands/enter-mission.ts` | Enter an existing mission context |\n| `/exit-mission` | `commands/exit-mission.ts` | Exit current mission context |\n\n## Implementation\n\nMission management spans several layers:\n- **CLI** -- `src/commands/missions.ts` (8330 lines) handles mission lifecycle, `src/task/` manages sub-agent spawning\n- **Frontend** -- `packages/frontend/src/features/missions/` provides the mission UI\n- **Common** -- type definitions for mission state and sub-task results\n- **Daemon** -- manages mission session coordination\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/missions.ts` | Mission listing and management |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/enter-mission.ts` | Mission entry |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/exit-mission.ts` | Mission exit |\n| `apps/cli/src/task/` | Sub-agent task management |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/missions/` | Mission UI |\n",
