            "content": "# Session\n\nA session represents a single conversation between a user and Droid. It is the central data object in the platform, referenced by the CLI, daemon, frontend, backend, and data models.\n\n## Where it appears\n\n| System | How it's used |\n|---|---|\n| CLI | `SessionService.ts` manages the active session, `ConversationStateManager.ts` tracks message history |\n| Daemon | Routes messages to the correct CLI process per session |\n| Frontend | `DaemonSessionController.ts` manages the WebSocket session, `features/sessions/` renders the UI |\n| Backend | API routes for session CRUD, Firestore persistence |\n| Common | Type definitions in `src/session/` and `src/sessionV2/` |\n| Models | Firestore model in `src/session/` |\n\n## Key fields\n\nA session typically includes:\n- **Session ID** -- unique identifier\n- **Organization ID** -- owning organization\n- **User ID** -- creating user\n- **Title** -- user-facing name (auto-generated or user-set)\n- **Messages** -- conversation history\n- **Model** -- LLM model used\n- **Created/updated timestamps**\n- **Tags** -- user-applied tags\n- **Favorite** -- boolean flag\n- **Status** -- active, ended, archived\n\n## Session vs session V2\n\nThe codebase has both `src/session/` and `src/sessionV2/` directories in `@factory/common`. The V2 types appear to represent an evolution of the session model, likely introduced to support new features like missions or improved message storage.\n",
