            "content": "# Message\n\nA message is a single unit of conversation within a session. Messages have roles (user, assistant, tool) and can contain text content, tool calls, or tool results.\n\n## Message structure\n\nMessages follow the LLM conversation format:\n- **User messages** -- text input from the user\n- **Assistant messages** -- LLM responses, which may include text and/or tool calls\n- **Tool messages** -- results from tool execution, returned to the LLM\n\n## Tool calls in messages\n\nWhen the LLM wants to use a tool, the assistant message includes a tool call block specifying:\n- Tool name (e.g., \"Read\", \"Execute\", \"Edit\")\n- Parameters (file path, command, etc.)\n- A tool call ID for matching results\n\nThe tool result message includes:\n- The matching tool call ID\n- The output (file contents, command output, etc.)\n- Success or error status\n\n## Where messages are defined\n\nMessage types live in `packages/common/src/droid/` (for the protocol-level message format) and `packages/common/src/session/` (for the persisted message format). The CLI's `ConversationStateManager` in `apps/cli/src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` manages the in-memory message array during a session. The `packages/droid-core/src/messages/` directory handles format conversion between internal and provider-specific formats.\n",
