            "content": "# How to contribute\n\nThis section covers the process and conventions for contributing to the Factory monorepo.\n\n## Work pickup\n\nTasks are tracked in Linear. Each task has a ticket ID (e.g., `FAC-1234`) that must be referenced in the PR description.\n\n## PR process\n\n1. Create a feature branch from `dev` (the default branch)\n2. Make changes, write tests, run `npm run fix` and `npm run typecheck`\n3. Open a PR with title in Conventional Commits format: `type(scope): description`\n4. Include the Linear ticket in the PR description (e.g., `Closes FAC-1234`)\n5. Request review from relevant code owners\n6. Address review feedback\n7. Merge after approval\n\n## Definition of done\n\n- Code passes `npm run fix`, `npm run typecheck`, and relevant tests\n- New API endpoints have types in `@factory/common`\n- New UI components use `@factory/core-ui` primitives\n- PR follows the template in `.github/pull_request_template.md`\n\n## Pages in this section\n\n- [Development workflow](./development-workflow.md) -- branch, code, test, PR, merge cycle\n- [Testing](./testing.md) -- test frameworks, patterns, and execution\n- [Debugging](./debugging.md) -- logs, common errors, troubleshooting\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md) -- coding style, error handling, file organization\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md) -- build system, linters, CI\n",
