            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch strategy\n\nThe default branch is `dev`. All feature branches are created from and merged into `dev`. Release branches are cut from `dev` to `main` for production deployments.\n\nBranch naming: `<username>/<feature-description>` (e.g., `jla/wiki-dashboard-link`).\n\n## Development cycle\n\n1. **Branch**: Create a feature branch from `dev`\n2. **Code**: Make changes following the [patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md)\n3. **Test**: Run relevant tests (`npm run test -- --filter=@factory/<package>`)\n4. **Lint**: Run `npm run fix` to auto-fix lint and formatting issues\n5. **Typecheck**: Run `npm run typecheck` to verify TypeScript\n6. **PR**: Open a pull request with Conventional Commits title\n7. **Review**: Address feedback from code owners\n8. **Merge**: Squash merge after approval\n\n## Local development\n\nStart the full development stack:\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web      # Backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon\nnpm run dev:desktop  # Same + desktop app (local only)\n```\n\nFor CLI development:\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup  # Build CLI, creates droid-dev wrapper\n```\n\nSee [Getting started](../overview/getting-started.md) for detailed setup.\n\n## PR conventions\n\n**Title format**: `type(scope): description`\n- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n- Scope: workspace name (`cli`, `backend`, `frontend`) or `monorepo`\n\n**Description**: Must include Linear ticket reference. Follow the template in `.github/pull_request_template.md`.\n",
