            "content": "# Testing\n\n## Frameworks\n\n| App/Package | Framework | Config |\n|---|---|---|\n| Backend (`apps/backend`) | Jest | `jest.config.js` |\n| CLI (`apps/cli`) | Jest | `jest.config.js` |\n| Frontend packages | Vitest | `vite.config.ts` |\n| E2E (web) | Playwright | `playwright.config.ts` |\n\n## Running tests\n\n```bash\n# All tests (heavy -- ~9 GB RAM)\nnpm run test\n\n# Filtered to specific packages\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# Single test file\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Frontend tests need jsdom\n\nAny test that uses browser APIs (React hooks, DOM, window) must include at the top:\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\n```\n\n## Mocking pattern\n\nMock at the top level, preserve non-mocked exports with `requireActual`:\n\n```typescript\njest.mock('./module', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./module'),\n  functionToMock: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\n## Singleton testing\n\nFor modules with singleton state, use module isolation:\n\n```typescript\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\n\nit('test', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // Fresh singleton per test\n});\n```\n\n## Key rules\n\n- Colocate tests with source files\n- Test the public API, not internals\n- Use absolute imports (`@/...`, `@factory/...`)\n- Keep pure utilities real (don't mock them)\n- New API endpoints need test coverage\n\nSee `docs/unit-tests.md` for the full testing guide.\n",
