            "content": "# Debugging\n\n## Log locations\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|---|---|---|\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | `daemon.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | Same files |\n| Dev servers | `/tmp/factory-dev-*.log` | `backend.log`, `admin.log`, `desktop.log`, `daemon.log` |\n\n## Quick checklist\n\nWhen changes aren't appearing or behavior is unexpected:\n\n1. Rebuilt CLI after changes? `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Restarted daemon process?\n3. Started a new session? (Old sessions don't pick up code changes)\n4. Checking the right log directory? (`~/.factory-dev/` for dev, not `~/.factory/`)\n5. Schema/enum changes are in `@factory/common`?\n6. Frontend handler exists for the notification type?\n\n## Message flow debugging\n\nTrace messages at each layer:\n\n```bash\n# Check CLI emitted the message\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# Watch logs in real-time\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/*.log\n```\n\n## Common issues\n\n### Timing\n\nNotifications sent before the session is registered with the daemon are lost. Always emit notifications after session initialization completes.\n\n### Schema mismatches\n\nIf the CLI sends a notification but the frontend doesn't receive it:\n1. Notification type is in `SessionNotificationType` enum (`packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`)\n2. Schema is defined in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. Frontend handler exists in `DaemonSessionController.ts`\n\n### Adding debug logging\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo } from '@factory/logging';\nlogInfo('[Feature] Event received', { count: items.length });\n```\n\nSee `docs/debugging-daemon.md` for the full debugging guide.\n",
