            "content": "# API\n\nThe Factory backend exposes a REST API via Next.js API routes. All endpoints require authentication via WorkOS session tokens passed in request headers.\n\n## Endpoint groups\n\n| Group | Path prefix | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| Sessions | `/api/sessions` | Session CRUD, message history, session search |\n| Auth | `/api/auth` | Login, logout, token refresh |\n| LLM | `/api/llm` | LLM proxy for streaming completions |\n| Billing | `/api/billing` | Subscription, usage, invoices |\n| Integrations | `/api/integrations` | Integration CRUD, OAuth flows |\n| Organizations | `/api/organizations` | Org management, member management |\n| Settings | `/api/settings` | User and org settings |\n| Droids | `/api/droids` | Custom droid configuration |\n| Webhooks | `/api/webhooks` | Webhook receivers for integrations |\n\n## Type conventions\n\nAPI request and response types are defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`. This pattern is enforced by ESLint and ensures type safety between frontend and backend.\n\nExample:\n```typescript\n// packages/common/src/api/sessions/types.ts\nexport interface CreateSessionRequest {\n  title?: string;\n  modelId?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface CreateSessionResponse {\n  sessionId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n## Frontend routes\n\nThe `AppRoutes` object in `apps/backend/src/routes.ts` defines all frontend route paths:\n- `/` -- dashboard\n- `/sessions` -- session list\n- `/sessions/:id` -- individual session\n- `/settings/*` -- settings pages (general, integrations, billing, API keys, security)\n- `/droids` -- custom droid management\n- `/login`, `/logout` -- auth pages\n\n## Middleware\n\n`apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` processes all requests:\n- Validates WorkOS session tokens\n- Applies rate limiting\n- Sets CORS headers\n- Logs request metadata\n\nSee [Backend](../apps/backend/index.md) for implementation details.\n",
