        {
          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "Create",
          "input": {
            "content": "# Logging\n\n## Logging functions\n\nAll logging goes through `@factory/logging`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo('Event processed', { count: 5 });\nlogWarn('Rate limit approaching', { usage: 950, limit: 1000 });\nlogException(error, 'Request failed', { userId: '123' });\n```\n\n- `logInfo` -- informational breadcrumbs for debugging\n- `logWarn` -- non-breaking warnings that should be monitored\n- `logException` -- error logging with full stack traces. If you call this, handle the error locally (no rethrow).\n\nThere is no `logError` function. Errors are either thrown (using `MetaError` or `ResponseErrorXXX`) or logged with `logException`.\n\n## Secret scrubbing\n\nThe logging system automatically scrubs sensitive data (API keys, tokens, passwords) from log output before sending to Sentry. This happens transparently in the logging infrastructure.\n\n## Sentry\n\nError tracking uses Sentry (`@sentry/node` for backend, `@sentry/nextjs` for Next.js). The CLI has its own Sentry configuration in `apps/cli/src/sentry.config.ts`.\n\nSentry receives:\n- Exceptions logged via `logException`\n- Unhandled errors\n- Breadcrumbs from `logInfo`/`logWarn` calls\n\n## Log locations\n\nSee [Debugging](../how-to-contribute/debugging.md) for log file paths.\n\n## Axiom\n\nAxiom is used for log aggregation across production systems. CLI and backend logs are shipped to Axiom for querying and alerting.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/logging/` | Logging infrastructure |\n| `apps/cli/src/sentry.config.ts` | CLI Sentry setup |\n| `apps/backend/src/instrumentation.ts` | Backend Sentry setup |\n| `docs/metrics-logging.md` | Metrics and logging guide |\n",
            "file_path": "/Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/droid-wiki/how-to-monitor/logging.md"
          },
          "timestamp": "2026-03-18T19:48:13.088Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "Create",
          "input": {
            "content": "# Metrics\n\n## Metrics system\n\nThe codebase uses a `Metrics` class from `@factory/logging` for recording application metrics:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Metrics } from '@factory/logging';\nimport { Metric } from '@factory/logging/metrics/enums';\n\nMetrics.record(Metric.SESSION_CREATED, { orgId: '123' });\n```\n\nMetric names are defined as enums in `@factory/logging/metrics/enums`. Each metric has a name and optional metadata.\n\n## Datadog\n\nDatadog is used for infrastructure and application metrics. Available dashboards cover:\n- CI pipeline performance\n- API latency and error rates\n- Infrastructure resource usage\n- Service health\n\n## Segment analytics\n\nUser-facing analytics events are tracked via Segment in `apps/backend/src/services/segment/`. Events include session creation, tool usage, billing actions, and integration connections.\n\n## CLI telemetry\n\nThe CLI has its own telemetry system via `CliTelemetryClient` in `apps/cli/src/utils/cliTelemetryClient.ts`. It tracks session start times, command usage, and error rates.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/logging/` | Metrics recording infrastructure |\n| `apps/backend/src/services/segment/` | Segment analytics |\n| `apps/cli/src/utils/cliTelemetryClient.ts` | CLI telemetry |\n| `docs/metrics-logging.md` | Metrics and logging guide |\n",
