            "content": "# Configuration\n\n## Environment variables\n\nEnvironment variables are accessed through `@factory/environment` for type safety. The ESLint rule `no-direct-process-env` enforces this -- do not use `process.env` directly.\n\n```typescript\nimport { getEnv } from '@factory/environment';\nconst apiUrl = getEnv('FACTORY_API_URL');\n```\n\n## Key configuration files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `.nvmrc` | Node.js version (18.x) |\n| `package.json` | Workspace definitions, scripts, dependencies |\n| `tsconfig.json` | Base TypeScript configuration |\n| `turbo.json` | Turborepo task definitions and caching |\n| `knip.json` | Unused export detection config |\n| `firebase.json` | Firebase project configuration |\n| `firestore.rules` | Firestore security rules |\n| `firestore.indexes.json` | Firestore index definitions |\n| `.github/CODEOWNERS` | Code ownership for PR review routing |\n| `infra/mise.toml` | Infrastructure tool versions |\n\n## Settings system\n\nThe `@factory/services` package provides `SettingsManager` and `FactorySettingsFolder` for managing user and project settings. Settings are stored in `~/.factory/` (production) or `~/.factory-dev/` (development).\n\nProject-level settings can be placed in `.factory/` at the repository root.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flags are configured in Statsig and defined in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. See [Feature flags](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) for usage patterns.\n",
