            "content": "# Data models\n\n## Firestore models\n\nData models for Firestore are defined in `packages/models/src/`. Each model has a directory with type definitions and optional converter utilities.\n\n| Model | Directory | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| Organization | `organization/` | Multi-tenant org: members, settings, billing (21 files) |\n| Session | `session/` | Conversation sessions |\n| Session V2 | `sessionV2/` | Next-gen session model |\n| Integrations | `integrations/` | OAuth tokens and integration config |\n| API Keys | `factoryApiKeys/` | Factory API key management |\n| Referrals | `referrals/` | Referral program data |\n| Promotions | `promotions/` | Promotional offers |\n| Memory | `memory/` | Agent memory/context storage |\n| Events | `events/` | Tracked events |\n| Repositories | `repositories/` | Connected repository metadata |\n| Agent | `agent/` | Agent configuration |\n| Workspace | `workspace/` | Workspace settings |\n| Card fingerprints | `cardFingerprints/` | Payment card deduplication |\n| Deleted organization | `deletedOrganization/` | Soft-deleted org data |\n\n## API type contracts\n\nAPI request/response types live in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`. This convention ensures frontend and backend agree on data shapes. See `docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md` for examples.\n\n## Protocol schemas\n\nThe JSON-RPC protocol schemas in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` and `packages/common/src/daemon/` define the message format between CLI, daemon, and frontend. See [Protocol](../packages/common/protocol.md).\n",
